    This is a great adjustment. It makes the advertising contextually relevant. By placing the ad exactly where the user's eyes will go when using the actual extension, you are reinforcing the "sidebar" concept visually.

To achieve this, we need to change the layout structure of your <main> area from a single column to a two-column flex layout (main content on left, sidebar on right).

Here is the plan:

HTML Structure: Wrap your existing .projects section and a new <aside> sidebar section inside a new parent flex container.

CSS Layout: Tell the existing project grid to take up roughly 75% of the width, and the new sidebar to take the remaining 25%.

Visual Polish: Style the sidebar to look like a distinct "tool" panel, and add position: sticky so it stays visible as the user scrolls down the page.

1. Update views/index.ejs
